The paper deals with feature distribution learning (FDL) and information-theoretic tools to assess the quality of the learning process. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
